article.description: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -Ruell Pringle and Jonathan Rodriguez scored career-high totals Monday to lead the Campbell Camels to a 100-94 win over the UNC Wilmington Seahawks.
article.headline: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -Ruell Pringle and Jonathan Rodriguez scored career-high totals Monday to lead the Campbell Camels to a 100-94 win over the UNC Wilmington Seahawks.
article.linkText: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -Ruell Pringle and Jonathan Rodriguez scored career-high totals Monday to lead the Campbell Camels to a 100-94 win over the UNC Wilmington Seahawks.
article.story: Pringle hit 9-12 field goals, including two three-pointers, for 27 points. Rodriguez was 8-17 with one three-pointer for 22 points. It was the 3-0 Camels first win over the 1-2 Seahawks in nearly 11 years and the first time Campbell scored 100 points against a Division I opponent since 1979 when it beat Charleston Southern. Wilmington led 50-38 at the half but was outscored 62-44 in the second half by Campbell as the Camels hit 56 percent. The lead in the second half changed three times and the score was tied seven times. Temi Soyebo led the Seahawks with 23 points, including four three-pointers, and Vladimir Kuljanin had 21 points, shooting 10-16 from the floor.
